A person swims in the waves at Muizenberg beach, a popular swimming and surfing venue, which is part of False Bay in Cape Town on November 17, 2020. JOHANNESBURG - The Northern Cape will be the only place in the country where people can go to the beach. Public parks and recreational facilities across the country will be closed. This is with the exception of botanical gardens, zoos and aquariums. READ : SUMMARY: SA to move to Level 3 Lockdown from midnight Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs minister, Dr Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma made the announcement during a media briefing on Tuesday. Hotel, lodges and BnBs will remain open.